> Your favorite sandwich now comes in loaded salad form: Crisp baby lettuce, juicy tomato, and crisp, smoky bacon—unite! Add in shredded white cheddar and toss it all together with tangy, creamy Dijon-infused blue cheese dressing and a sprinkle of smoky bacon fat-toasted panko breadcrumbs to take this sumptuous salad right over the top!

Heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop. Discard all but a thin layer of bacon fat from pan.

While bacon cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{2}; chop into bite-size pieces. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @blue cheese dressing{1.5%ounce}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} until smooth.

Return pan with reserved bacon fat to medium-high heat (if pan seems dry, add a drizzle of oil). Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Add lettuce, tomatoes, and half the @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}(shredded) to bowl with vinaigrette; toss to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide salad between #bowls{}; garnish with remaining cheddar, chopped bacon, and toasted panko. Serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.